# Use ARCHITECTURE.md as the code map

[`ARCHITECTURE.md`](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) (repo root) is the navigational map of this codebase.

## Finding code

- **Before broadly searching the codebase, consult `ARCHITECTURE.md`.** It lists the top-level
  layout, the most important files, the game-engine data flow, and "where does X live" tables.
- Use it to jump straight to the right file (e.g. game state → `client/src/game/state.ts`,
  the loop → `client/src/game/loop.ts`, persisted schema → `shared/schema.ts`,
  API routes → `server/index.ts`).

## Keeping it current

When you **add, remove, rename, or move files/directories** under `client/`, `server/`,
`shared/`, `supabase/`, `scripts/`, or `gender-service/`, or change a core architectural
fact (engine flow, persistence, routing, tech stack), **update the matching section/table in
`ARCHITECTURE.md` in the same change.**

A `stop` hook (`.cursor/hooks/architecture-update-check.mjs`) detects structural changes and will
ask you to refresh `ARCHITECTURE.md` if you forget — keep entries accurate and concise (paths +
one-line responsibilities), don't duplicate the full style guide in `.cursorrules`.
